@ScrubbyCEO @conanahere Great discussion @ScrubbyCEO and @conanahere. I can see both sides of the picture. I am leaning towards being more optimistic as we are earlier half of the crypto adoption curve

@ScrubbyCEO They can leave, which is part of the decentralized nature of DAOs. Nothing ties them here.

Projects where communities stay and build and gets reinvested will succeed. Bayc is not the norm. Its the anomaly
@ScrubbyCEO I would like to think that because apes own their own IP, they can interpret and build around that IP, as compared to management or shareholders directing a company.
@ScrubbyCEO I see your point. I think in the case of BAYC the community was very strong from the start. Apes were following each other on twitter, many spun off their own projects.

@ScrubbyCEO With DAOs and NFTs, we are seeing decentralized communities coming together to build a brand out of the projects they are like/invested in. This is a shift from traditional centralized corps and businesses
